Key Components:

    MQ Subscriber: Listens to the IBM MQ queue.
    POCO Model: Represents the structure of the incoming XML message.
    XML to POCO Converter: Converts the incoming XML message to a POCO model using XPath.
    Database Writer: Converts the POCO model to SQL instructions using Dapper.
    Reconnection Logic: Handles reconnection attempts for both MQ and the database.
    Multithreading: Processes each message in a separate thread.
    Logging: Logs information using a logger framework like NLog or Log4Net.
    Unit Testing: Test methods to verify correctness.
